B139 — LEGENDARY DAWNSONG RELICS (HEALER · LV 60)

Now a healer-focused legendary pair, so support specs have a chase path:

Dawnsong Covenant — 1H healer mace.

Heartroot Reliquary — healer trinket or off-hand (I’ll make it a trinket; off-hand slot is crowded).

1. Dawnsong Covenant (Legendary Healer Mace)
1.1 Item Definition

Dawnsong Covenant
Level 60 · 1H Mace · Legendary
“Forged from every prayer whispered in Emberwild’s worst nights.”

Stats:

+40 Intellect

+34 Spirit

+30 Stamina

+72 Spell Power

+2% Healing Done

+8 Mana per 5 sec

Passive — Dawnsong Chorus:

Your single-target healing spells apply Dawnsong Chorus to the target for 8 sec:

While active, 10% of your overhealing on that target becomes a small shield instead of being fully wasted (up to a cap).

Internal cooldown per target: 12 sec (so you can’t spam infinite shields).

Passive — Covenant of Respite:

When any party or raid member falls below 30% HP:

Your next healing spell cast within 6 seconds has +20% increased healing.

Internal cooldown: 20 sec.

1.2 Acquisition — The Dawnsong Vigil

Questline name: “The Dawnsong Vigil”

Fantasy: You’re healing important NPCs / events in each zone, not killing things.

Step 1 — Wardens of the Wild

Objectives:

Greatwood: Keep a Warden of Heartroot alive through waves of Blightspore / Widow attacks.

Ashen Ridge: Keep a Forge-Priest alive as they stabilize a runaway furnace.

Frostmarch: Heal/cleanse a Frostmarch Hermit during a ritual to calm a blizzard.

Duskhollow: Protect a Duskhollow Penitent as they atone in a shadow ritual.

Each success grants:

One “Dawnsong Memory” corresponding to the zone.

Turn in all four to a central priest NPC, High Cantor Elyndra.

Reward:

“Unbound Dawnsong Mace Head” (quest item, not equip).

Next quest.

Step 2 — Binding the Covenant

Objectives:

Perform three Covenant Rites in your hubs or shrines:

Rite of Ember — Ashen Ridge altar.

Rite of Frost — Frostmarch altar.

Rite of Shadow — Duskhollow altar.

Each rite:

Spawns ghostly echoes of NPCs you saved; you must keep them alive during an echo fight.

After all three:

Your mace head becomes “Tempered Dawnsong Covenant” (unfinished weapon object).

Next quest: “The Long Night’s End.”

Step 3 — The Long Night’s End (Instance)

Instance: “The Long Night” — defense scenario.

Wave-based event:

Players defend a mixed group of NPCs from all zones (Heartroot guardian, Forge-Priest, Hermit, Penitent).

If too many die, fail.

Mechanics:

Darkened sky, shadow/frost spawns.

Periodic pulses that pressure healers.

Healer must juggle:

Direct healing,

Cleanses,

Movement.

Success:

Tempered Dawnsong Covenant → Dawnsong Covenant (equippable Legendary).

1.3 Quest Skeleton (Lua)
Quests["LEGENDARIES.DAWNSONG_COVENANT"] = {
    id       = "Q_LEGENDARY_DAWNSONG",
    name     = "The Dawnsong Vigil",
    levelReq = 60,

    steps = {
        {
            id = 1,
            description = "Keep Emberwild's wardens alive through their darkest trials.",
            subSteps = {
                { id = "WARDEN_HEARTROOT",   scenario = "SCENARIO_WARDEN_HEARTROOT"   },
                { id = "WARDEN_FORGEPRIEST", scenario = "SCENARIO_WARDEN_FORGEPRIEST" },
                { id = "WARDEN_HERMIT",      scenario = "SCENARIO_WARDEN_HERMIT"      },
                { id = "WARDEN_PENITENT",    scenario = "SCENARIO_WARDEN_PENITENT"    },
            },
