            },
            nextStep = 3,
        },
        {
            id = 3,
            description = "Endure the Long Night and protect the faithful.",
            instance = "INSTANCE_LONG_NIGHT",
            finalBoss = "BOSS_NIGHTFALL_ASPECT",
            reward = {
                items = { { id = "ITEM_DAWNSONG_COVENANT", count = 1 } },
            },
            nextStep = nil,
        },
    },
}

2. Heartroot Reliquary (Legendary Healer Trinket)
2.1 Item Definition

Heartroot Reliquary
Level 60 · Trinket · Legendary

Stats:

+24 Intellect

+20 Spirit

+18 Stamina

+1% Healing Done

Passive — Roots of Recovery:

Your periodic healing effects (HoTs) on a target have a small chance to:

Bloom, instantly healing them for a chunk of the remaining HoT value.

Internal cooldown per target: 15 sec.

Use — Heartroot Bloom (2 min CD):

For 12 seconds:

Your HoTs tick 30% faster, but their duration is reduced accordingly (so total healing stays similar, but delivered much faster).

This is a strong “tempo button” for raid healing without straight-up adding absurd HPS.

2.2 Acquisition — Optional Side Chain

You can either:

Make it part of Dawnsong Covenant chain as a bonus if you complete optional challenges, or

Give it a small side-quest:

Quest Idea: “Echoes of the First Grove”

Heal and cleanse corrupted Heartroot trees in Greatwood and a couple other zones.

Final event: restore a Heartroot sapling in your endgame hub, which becomes a sanctuary tree.

Reward: Heartroot Reliquary.

You can decide whether this is:

A pure quest reward,

Or has very low drop chance from a special “First Grove Shade” boss.
